postcontent:
Up for sale is a professionally assembled custom rifle.  I am a Police M-16/AR-15 armorer certified by Colt.  This custom build was put together using Larue Tactical upper and lower receivers, Daniel Defense handguard, Geissele trigger, and the very hard to find Lothar Walther 300blk barrel from Spikes Tactical.  All parts were assembled brand new and not cannibalized from other builds. 

I hate to part with this rifle because it is a lot of fun to shoot and the 300blk is such a neat round to research and play around with.  Just look at the parts list and do the math, you’ll see that no expense was spared when this rifle was being meticulously built and my price reflects the parts installed.  This rifle is extremely lightweight. And as with any billet Larue upper/lower receiver it is super tight” Tex-spec”.  There is absolutely no play or slop between the upper and lower receivers at all. 

Approximately 164 rounds have been shot through the barrel and have been documented in a data log book which is included with the sale. Also I have saved almost every spent casing as well as every empty box of ammo fired through the rifle.

I’ll be including over 350 rounds of ammo with this sale (approximately $400 value). 

Also if you’re interested, I have thousands of pieces of 223/556 brass (all once fired Federal).  I have more brass than I know what to do with.  This could be easily reloaded into 300blk.  If you want I can include some brass with the sale of the rifle plus I’ll throw in a brand new set of dies used to reload .300BLK…

title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch P2000 SK Pistol
postcontent: The P2000 is a short recoil-operated locked breech pistol with a modified Browning-type linkless cam action with a vertically tilting barrel also employed in the USP series of self-loading pistols, as well as most modern linkless semi autos. The cold hammer-forged barrel has a polygonal profile while the slide is made from a solid bar of nitro-carburized steel. Following recent trends in modern pistol design, the P2000 makes extensive use of impact-resistant polymers to reduce weight and production costs. As with other recent Heckler & Koch pistol designs, the P2000 is modular to suit individual needs. For instance, the grip is modular with exchangeable backstraps, allowing the user to customize the pistol's grip size and feel. There is a universal accessory rail built into the dust cover in front of the trigger guard that allows for the use of tactical lights, laser pointers and other accessories. This is in contrast with the USP series which uses a proprietary H&K mounting rail that limits the types of accessories that could be used with the pistol. The P2000 is a hammer-fired pistol with an exposed spurred hammer; a bobbed hammer is optional. It has an ambidextrous slide lock and a fully ambidextrous magazine release installed in the trigger guard.

title: For Sale:  Kimber TLE II 10mm LNIB
postcontent:
I have an almost brand-new Kimber Tactical Law Enforcement (TLE) chambered for 10mm. I bought this gun new from Sportsmans Warehouse in February, and I bought this particular one because it is a little tighter and more solid feeling than most Kimbers I've felt, and also turned out to be extremely accurate too. I've put less than 500 rounds through it so far, so it's not even broken in yet. There are virtually no signs of wear or marks. The night sights are probably the brightest I've seen on any gun so far. Only selling because I don't use it enough and need cash.

I also added an increased power Wolff mainspring (not recoil spring) to help mitigate the recoil of some hotter 10mm loads, which I never ended up using in this gun. I also added an EGW flat bottom firing pin stop, which fits better than the original Kimber one. The combination of the heavier mainspring and flat bottom firing pin stop help reduce recoil and negate the increased wear that comes from using full-power rounds. For more info on why I did this check out this thread: http://10mm-firearms.com/general-discussion/1911-owners-we-are-doing-it-wrong!/

Comes with the original box and all the goodies that come with that, as well as an extra Kimber mag for a total of two mags, and the original firing pin stop. Asking $1,000 obo, which is a bit less than I paid for this (Gun alone was $1070, mag $40, and other parts were $34).

Thanks for looking!

This is a Series 80 descendant of the 1911A1 with firing pin safety, but also with full coverage military style finish, brown Bakelite type GI Grips, and a lanyard ring type Mainspring Housing. Manufacturer is Colt Industries of Hartford, CT. Exclusive distributor is Lew Horton Distributing of Westboro, MA. Colt factory designation is Model O1991Z, M1991A1 Series 80. Construction is entirely steel, with the exception of the grips, and the anodized trigger and mainspring housing. The Colt M1991A1, writes the factory, is a direct 4th generation descendant of the "often imitated but never duplicated" Colt M1911 classic automatic pistol, and this variant is the closest approximation to the World War II version. Type is Browning Design 1911 Government type Single Action semi-automatic pistol. Chambering is .45 ACP Caliber. Barrel is 5 inch stainless, 6 groove left hand 1:16 rifling. Frame and slide finish are matte blue, approximating the WWII parkerized versions. Sight system is matte blue stake on front and dovetailed notch style rear that is drift adjustable only for windage. Safety system is classic threefold, main safety for right handed shooters; grip safety; and Series 80 type firing pin safety. Each 1991 comes with a total of two factory magazines, Colt factory marked and made for Colt by primary supplier Check-Mate. Each magazine holds 7 rounds, so 7 + 1 fully loaded capacity, and 8 shot magazines are readily available from us and throughout the country. Weight empty is 35 ounces with center of gravity at the magazine release. Trigger is .250 serrated face alloy, and the photo specimen pulled in the 6 pound vicinity with minimal felt creep. Each pistol comes in a current production Colt blue box with instruction manual, cable lock, factory registration paper, total of two magazines, chamber protector, and protective wrapper. Each also contains a total of two grips, one set the pliable black rubber factory Rampant Colt grips and traditional WWII to Vietnam issue type brown plastic. Each one ships with the black rubber, and the owner can easily change them to the brown like we did on the photo specimen.
